Confronting the consequences of racism, xenophobia, and discrimination on health and health-care systems.
Actions need to consider the historical, economic, and political contexts in which the effects of racism, xenophobia, and discrimination affect health. We propose several specific actions: a commission that explores how we action the approaches laid out in this paper;  building a conversation and a series of events with international multilateral agency stakeholders to raise the issue and profile of racism, xenophobia, and discrimination within health;  and using our multiple platforms to build coalitions, expand knowledge, highlight inequities, and advocate for change across the world.
